s.text: The emphasis on sidewalks and walkability, the traditional design of the houses, the smaller lots that give a sense of place to the streets, the back alleys that put the cars in the background, and the planning that gives equal importance to the individual houses and the common shared spaces.
If I lived in Celebration, I would have to drive some distance to find one.
So much of what is necessary to the way we live today is relegated to "out there."
One of the students wrote: "If there was one question I would like to ask the people who live in these neotraditional communities, it would be: What would it take to make you move?"
